                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Inclosure.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Panama Railroad Company</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Minister of Panama</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">New York</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-03-28">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 28, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Sir</hi>: We acknowledge receipt of your letter of the
                    20th instant requesting the approval of this Company under Article II of the
                    Contract of 1867 between the Panama Railroad Co. and the United States of
                    Colombia to the construction by the Government of the Republic of Panama of a
                    railroad in the Province of Chiriquí and another in the Province of Los
                    Santos.</p>
                <p>We take pleasure in advising that at a meeting of the board of directors of our
                    Company held on the 25th instant, the following resolution was unanimously
                    adopted: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="italic">Resolved</hi> that the Panama Railroad Company hereby
                            consents to the construction by the Government of the Republic of Panama
                            of the following lines of railroad:</p>
                        <p>One in the Province of Chiriquí, from the port of Pedregal to Boquete, 28
                            miles, with a branch to La Concepción, 23 miles.</p>
                        <p>One in the Province of Los Santos, from the port of Mensabe to the town
                            of Macaracas.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">E. A. Drake</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
